Peel and stick wallpaper- Just a couple things I learned along the way yesterday 😂 Other things to add- this wallpaper had been on the wall for 4 years, it was purchased from Target, I didn’t use anything to help take it down (with exception of a blow dryer) so maybe I should’ve done several things differently… 🤔 
Tell me your experiences with taking down peel and stick wallpaper! Did I do everything wrong?! 🤣
——————————————————————————————————
#peelandstickwallpaper 
#peelandstick

Am I crazy? Maybe 😂 honestly, if I would have been better prepared, it wouldn’t have been so bad. 
I learned a lot! If you plan to take down wallpaper anytime soon, here’s what you need to know! 

-Peel and stick is not like traditional wallpaper. It needs to be peeled off with your hands. DO NOT use heat. It leaves the sticky residue from wallpaper on the wall and then you have to scrub it off. No fun🤪

-Invest in high quality wallpaper. The wallpaper I took down was purchased from Target and I’m sure if I had used something better quality it wouldn’t have been so bad so take down. 

-I’ve been told peel and stick wallpaper is only guaranteed damage free for the first year. After that, this could happen to your walls. 

I hope this helps anyone considering wallpaper!
